Thought by many to be the inspiration for the TV series 'Mission: Impossible',
Jules Dassin's comedy-thriller follows a group of art thieves as they plot and
plan to rob a jewelled dagger from the fortress-like Topkapi Palace museum in
sun-soaked Istanbul. With an international cast and a screenplay written by
ex-Ealing stalwart Monja Danischewsky, 'Topkapi' is one of the great
comic-exotic heist movies.

